  "prompt": "What is a cake mix?",
  "response": "A cake mix is a pre-packaged blend of ingredients designed to simplify the process of baking cakes. Typically, it contains flour, sugar, baking powder, and flavorings. Some mixes may include powdered milk or chocolate chips. To prepare a cake with a cake mix, you generally need to add a few additional ingredients, such as eggs, oil, and water, followed by mixing and baking as directed on the package. Cake mixes are convenient and help ensure consistency in baking results.",
